      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T07:58:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e \u003e I think we might be acking too eagerly here.\n\u003e \u003e \n\u003e \u003e `broker.send()` is asynchronous\n\u003e \n\u003e The lines of code do not call `broker.send()` but `requeueAction.requeue(event)` which must be synchronous.\nTrue.\nThe requeueAction.requeue(event), however is implemented `MultiSiteConsumerRunner.javaL85`\n\n```\n(e) -\u003e broker.send(topic, e)\n```\n\n\u003e \n\u003e The comment should be for the block where the `requeueAction` is implemented.\n\u003e \n\u003e \u003e but `RequeueEventAction` returns `void`, so we acknowledge the original but we don\u0027t know whether the new copy was published successfully and ff the publish fails, the event is lost.\n\u003e \n\u003e Good point, so we need to ensure that `requeueAction` returns a `boolean` and ack the message *only if* the requeue was successful.\n\nYes, makes sense to me.",
      "parentUuid": "1ca5b532_55501b2f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 124,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 125,
        "endChar": 48
