        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-16T17:10:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Publishing a new copy here and breaking the ordering of the events seems wrong to me.\n\nIf the partition contains:\n```\nDELETE(A) → INDEX(A)\n```\n\nand `DELETE(A)` returns `RETRY`, we republish it at the end and acknowledge the original. The partition then become:\n\n```\nINDEX(A) → DELETE(A)\n```\n\nSo the newer index may succeed first, followed by the older delete, leaving the final index state wrong.\n\nCan we discuss about this?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 85,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5350343f_a2e14ee1",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/plugins/multisite/consumer/MultiSiteConsumerRunner.java",
        "patchSetId": 64
      },
      "lineNbr": 85,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000000
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T07:20:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This isn\u0027t an event-source system, but a reindexing propagation of entities replicated using the Git protocol.\n\nThe cause you\u0027re mentioning isn\u0027t realistic: how can you reindex a deleted entity?\n\nWhat it *could* happen is: `INDEX(A)` + `DELETE(A)` may become `DELETE(A)` + `INDEX(A)`.\n\nThe final state is that the entity is deleted, which is correct. So I don\u0027t see any issues here.",
      "parentUuid": "a9b131b5_65c39e09",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 85,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
