      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T07:58:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e This isn\u0027t an event-source system, but a reindexing propagation of entities replicated using the Git protocol.\n\u003e \n\u003e The cause you\u0027re mentioning isn\u0027t realistic: how can you reindex a deleted entity?\n\nYou can achieve this by deleting and recreating the same entity, that will translate to DELETE from the index and then INDEX again, no?.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e What it *could* happen is: `INDEX(A)` + `DELETE(A)` may become `DELETE(A)` + `INDEX(A)`.\n\u003e \n\u003e The final state is that the entity is deleted, which is correct. So I don\u0027t see any issues here.",
      "parentUuid": "5350343f_a2e14ee1",
